  <span id="freeText16773479686918661307" style="display:none">Wow, I had no idea that F. Scott Fitzgerald practiced writing The Great Gatsby by writing a ton of short stories with the same theme. Poor boy, rich girl...ugh. Don't get me wrong. I love The Great Gatsby and I LOVE the way Fitzgerald writes, but I got hung up so long on that string of "Gatsby Stories" I didn't finish the book before the library said I had too many renewals...meaning I had the book for over 2 months and had to turn it in. I will come back and finish it someday. There are a few real gems in there. The Offshore Pirate alone makes it a book worth reading. </span>
