              <span id="reviewTextContainer2451971048" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4451887564258210819">I liked about a third of the stories. I liked best Stockton&apos;s &quot;A Tale of Negative Gravity,&quot; Marryatt&apos;s &quot;The Werewolf&quot; (which is made all the better when you think about when it was written), Wodehouse&apos;s &quot;Providence and the Butler,&quot; and Hornung&apos;s &quot;To Catch a Thief.&quot; A few were decent, and a few others I simply didn&apos;t get into; but that is common with any collection. </span>
  <span id="freeText4451887564258210819" style="display:none">I liked about a third of the stories. I liked best Stockton's "A Tale of Negative Gravity," Marryatt's "The Werewolf" (which is made all the better when you think about when it was written), Wodehouse's "Providence and the Butler," and Hornung's "To Catch a Thief." A few were decent, and a few others I simply didn't get into; but that is common with any collection. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4451887564258210819" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


